Forgive me.

1034
01:12:08,453 --> 01:12:10,783
God forgive me.

1035
01:12:37,313 --> 01:12:39,843
...Our Lord Jesus Christ's sake.

1036
01:12:40,583 --> 01:12:43,023
One morning in the month of May>>

1037
01:12:43,083 --> 01:12:45,423
From my cot I stray>>

1038
01:12:46,223 --> 01:12:48,623
Just at the dawning of the day>>

1039
01:12:48,963 --> 01:12:51,693
I met with a charming mai-->>

1040
01:12:53,463 --> 01:12:56,733
You look sad, my lady. Let me take you riding.

1041
01:12:57,303 --> 01:13:00,763
- It's not my riding day, my lord. - Bless me, I thought it was a horse.

1042
01:13:00,975 --> 01:13:03,423
I'm going to church.

1043
01:13:03,473 --> 01:13:06,273
Of course. I understand. It is to be expected.

1044
01:13:07,283 --> 01:13:09,943
Yes, it is to be expected... on Sunday.

1045
01:13:10,783 --> 01:13:13,303
And on a day of mourning.

1046
01:13:14,153 --> 01:13:17,143
I never met the fellow but once at your house.

1047
01:13:17,575 --> 01:13:20,483
Mourning?

1048
01:13:21,328 --> 01:13:24,115
Who is dead, my lord?

1049
01:13:24,165 --> 01:13:29,086
Oh! Dear God, I did not think it would be me to tell you.

1050
01:13:29,603 --> 01:13:32,403
Great loss to playwriting and to dancing.

1051
01:13:34,925 --> 01:13:36,693
My lady.

1052
01:13:36,743 --> 01:13:39,733
- He is dead? - Killed last night in a tavern.

1053
01:13:42,043 --> 01:13:44,773
Come then. We'll say a prayer for his soul.

1054
01:13:49,857 --> 01:13:58,240
Who can remember sorrow>>

1055
01:14:29,293 --> 01:14:31,493
Spare me, dear ghost.

1056
01:14:31,633 --> 01:14:33,823
Spare me, dear ghost.

1057
01:14:34,463 --> 01:14:37,453
Spare me, for the love of Christ. Spare me!

1058
01:14:50,751 --> 01:14:53,843
Will!

1059
01:14:53,923 --> 01:14:56,040
Oh, my love.

1060
01:14:56,090 --> 01:14:59,153
I thought you were dead.

1061
01:15:03,063 --> 01:15:05,253
It is worse.

1062
01:15:05,863 --> 01:15:08,063
I've killed a man.

1063
01:15:12,303 --> 01:15:15,173
