1219
01:28:31,933 --> 01:28:34,663
and he drew from poets the literature of the age.

1220
01:28:36,743 --> 01:28:39,533
We must show them that we are men of parts.

1221
01:28:40,313 --> 01:28:43,043
Will Shakespeare has a play.

1222
01:28:43,813 --> 01:28:46,753
I have a theater. The curtain is yours.

1228
01:29:21,455 --> 01:29:26,153
Will! We'll be needing a Romeo.

1229
01:29:31,893 --> 01:29:34,293
Oranges! Sweet oranges!

1230
01:30:01,823 --> 01:30:05,553
My ship is moored at bankside, bound for Virginia on the afternoon tide.

1231
01:30:06,333 --> 01:30:08,243
Please do not weep, Lady De Lesseps.

1232
01:30:08,293 --> 01:30:10,233
You are gaining a colony.

1233
01:30:10,303 --> 01:30:13,163
And you, my lord, are gaining 5,000 pounds...>>

1234
01:30:13,233 --> 01:30:15,723
by these drafts in my hand.

1235
01:30:15,803 --> 01:30:18,573
Would you oblige me with 50 or so in gold...>>

1236
01:30:18,643 --> 01:30:21,633
just to settle my accounts at the dockside?

1237
01:30:23,225 --> 01:30:26,143
Ah, the bride!

1238
01:30:27,753 --> 01:30:30,083
Good morning, my lord.

1239
01:30:30,183 --> 01:30:33,183
I see you are... open for business, so let's to church.

1240
01:30:39,533 --> 01:30:41,485
Be gone!

1241
01:30:41,535 --> 01:30:43,662
Hup, hup, hup!

1243
01:31:39,653 --> 01:31:41,593
Oh, my lord!

1244
01:31:41,653 --> 01:31:44,253
- Be good to her, my lord. - I will.

1245
01:31:44,323 --> 01:31:46,423
Oh, God bless you!

1246
01:31:46,493 --> 01:31:49,363
Thank you. Uh, let go. There's a good nurse.

1247
01:31:49,433 --> 01:31:51,403
The tide will not wait!

1248
01:31:51,463 --> 01:31:54,263
Farewell! You'll all be welcome in Virginia!

1249
01:32:22,053 --> 01:32:25,093
Candy apples!

1250
01:32:26,603 --> 01:32:28,933
Buy my apples!

1251
01:32:34,857 --> 01:32:37,068
Thank you, sir. Apples!

1252
01:32:44,575 --> 01:32:47,987
