01:35:09,763 --> 01:35:12,423
whose misadventured, piteous overthrows...>>

1273
01:35:12,603 --> 01:35:15,863
doth with their death bury their parents' strife.

1274
01:35:19,243 --> 01:35:21,713
...the which of you with patient ears attend,>>

1275
01:35:22,413 --> 01:35:25,403
what here shall miss, our toil shall strive to mend.

1276
01:35:33,523 --> 01:35:36,043
- Wonderful. - Was it...>>

1277
01:35:36,663 --> 01:35:38,653
good?

1278
01:35:41,463 --> 01:35:44,403
Gregory, on my word we'll not carry coals.

1279
01:35:44,733 --> 01:35:47,533
No, for then we should be colliers.

1280
01:35:47,833 --> 01:35:50,363
I mean, and we be in choler we'll draw.

1281
01:35:50,443 --> 01:35:53,503
- Master Shakespeare. - Luck be with you, Sam. Sam!

1282
01:35:53,613 --> 01:35:56,073
It's not my fault. I could do it yesterday.

1283
01:35:56,143 --> 01:35:59,083
Do me a speech. Do me a line.

1284
01:35:59,413 --> 01:36:02,143
"Parting is such sweet sorrow.">>

1285
01:36:03,283 --> 01:36:06,483
- Another little problem. - What do we do now?

1286
01:36:06,623 --> 01:36:09,613
- The show must-- You know. - Go on!

1287
01:36:10,623 --> 01:36:14,063
Juliet does not come on for 20 pages. It will be all right.

1288
01:36:14,133 --> 01:36:17,323
- How will it? - I don't know. It's a mystery.

1289
01:36:21,503 --> 01:36:24,233
- Let them begin. - I will frown as I pass by.

1290
01:36:24,303 --> 01:36:27,763
- Let them take it as they list! - Nay, as they dare.

1291
01:36:28,213 --> 01:36:31,543
I will bite my thumb at them, which is disgrace to them if they bear it.

1292
01:36:32,553 --> 01:36:35,303
Do you bite your thumb at us, sir?

1293
01:36:35,353 --> 01:36:38,153
- I do bite my thumb, sir. - Excuse me. Thank you.

1294
01:36:38,723 --> 01:36:41,653
- Thank you. Excuse me. - Do you bite your thumb at us, sir?

1295
01:36:42,423 --> 01:36:44,363
- Can we talk? - Shh!

1296
01:36:44,423 --> 01:36:47,293
- We have no Juliet. - No Juliet?

1297
01:36:47,363 --> 01:36:50,423
- No Juliet? - It'll be all right, madam.

1298
01:36:50,503 --> 01:36:51,663
- What happened to Sam?

1299
01:36:51,733 --> 01:36:53,899
- Who are you? - Thomas Kent.

1300
01:36:53,949 --> 01:36:56,569
Do you know it?

1301
01:36:56,619 --> 01:37:00,503
- I serve as good a man as you. - Every word.

1302
01:37:03,584 --> 01:37:06,212
Hyah! Yah!

1303
01:37:09,753 --> 01:37:12,683
I'll go along, no such sight to be shown,>>

1304
01:37:12,853 --> 01:37:15,653
but to rejoice in splendor of mine own.

1305
01:37:16,053 --> 01:37:18,113
Nurse!

1306
01:37:20,733 --> 01:37:23,663
Where's my daughter? Call her forth to me.

1307
01:37:24,063 --> 01:37:26,793
Now, by my maidenhead at 12 years old,>>

1308
01:37:27,373 --> 01:37:29,303
I bade her come.

1309
01:37:29,373 --> 01:37:31,463
How now, who calls?

1310
01:37:31,543 --> 01:37:33,663
What, ladybird!

1311
01:37:34,373 --> 01:37:36,400
God forbid! Where's this girl?

1312
01:37:36,450 --> 01:37:38,893
What, lamb!

1313
01:37:38,943 --> 01:37:41,073
What, ladybird!

1314
01:37:42,213 --> 01:37:44,343
What, Juliet!

1315
01:37:45,783 --> 01:37:48,253
How now, who calls?

1316
01:37:52,341 --> 01:37:56,929
- We'll all be put in the Clink. - See you in jail.

1317
01:37:59,873 --> 01:38:02,393
Your mother-- Your mother.

1318
01:38:03,043 --> 01:38:05,973
Madam, I am here. What is your will?

1319
01:38:06,413 --> 01:38:08,463
This is the matter.

1320
01:38:08,543 --> 01:38:10,973
Nurse, give leave a while. We must talk in secret.

1321
01:38:11,043 --> 01:38:14,983
Nurse, come back again. I have remembered me; thou's hear our counsel.

1322
01:38:15,883 --> 01:38:18,413
Thou knowest my daughter's of a pretty age.

1323
01:38:19,323 --> 01:38:22,853
- Faith, I know her age unto an hour. - She's not 14.

1324
01:38:22,923 --> 01:38:26,253
Oh, I'll lay 14 of my teeth. And yet my teen be it spoken,>>

1325
01:38:28,493 --> 01:38:30,893
I have but four-->>

1326
01:38:53,493 --> 01:38:55,513
Tell me, daughter Juliet,>>

1327
01:38:55,593 --> 01:38:58,253
how stands your dispositions to be married?

1328
01:39:00,293 --> 01:39:02,823
It is an honor that I dream not of.

1329
01:39:07,633 --> 01:39:10,293
Hold, Tybalt! Good Mercutio!

1330
01:39:18,552 --> 01:39:21,563
I-- I'm sped.

1331
01:39:21,613 --> 01:39:24,413
Courage, man; the hurt cannot be much.

1332
01:39:24,483 --> 01:39:26,823
Ask for me tomorrow,>>

1333
01:39:26,923 --> 01:39:29,583
you shall find me a grave man.

1334
01:39:37,238 --> 01:39:40,491
Yes!

1335
01:39:45,746 --> 01:39:47,463
Yah!

1336
01:39:47,513 --> 01:39:49,973
"Such mortal drugs I have,>>

1337
01:39:50,143 --> 01:39:53,673
but Mantua's law is death to any he that utters them.">>

1338
01:39:54,913 --> 01:39:57,253
Then him. Then me.

1339
01:40:05,923 --> 01:40:08,023
Romeo, away, be gone!

1340
01:40:08,093 --> 01:40:11,363
The citizens are up, and Tybalt slain. Stand not amazed!

1341
01:40:12,603 --> 01:40:15,793
The prince will doom thee death if thou art taken. Hence, be gone, away!

1342
01:40:18,073 --> 01:40:20,443
Oh, I am Fortune's fool!

1343
01:40:20,513 --> 01:40:22,443
Why dost thou stay?

1344
01:40:22,513 --> 01:40:24,503
Which way ran he that killed Mercutio?

1345
01:40:24,583 --> 01:40:26,813
That murderer, which way ran he?

1346
01:40:26,883 --> 01:40:29,683
- There lies that Tybalt. - Up, sir. Go with me.

1347
01:40:29,753 --> 01:40:31,813
I charge thee in the Prince's name obey.

1348
01:40:31,883 --> 01:40:34,613
Where are the vile beginners of this fray?

1349
01:40:34,693 --> 01:40:37,213
"Oh, I am Fortune's fool.">>

1350
01:40:39,763 --> 01:40:42,163
You are married?

1351
01:40:45,333 --> 01:40:49,133
"lf you be married, my grave is like to be my wedding bed.">>

1352
01:41:06,123 --> 01:41:08,453
Art thou gone so,>>

1353
01:41:10,963 --> 01:41:13,083
Iove, lord,>>

1354
01:41:13,163 --> 01:41:15,393
aye, husband, friend?

1355
01:41:15,463 --> 01:41:18,193
I must hear from thee every day in the hour,>>

1356
01:41:20,303 --> 01:41:22,703
for in a minute there are many days.

1357
01:41:23,303 --> 01:41:26,503
Oh, by this count I shall be much in years ere again...>>

1358
01:41:26,973 --> 01:41:29,373
I behold my Romeo.

1359
01:41:29,683 --> 01:41:32,673
Farewell.

1360
01:41:32,913 --> 01:41:35,713
Oh, think'st thou we shall ever meet again?

1361
01:41:37,883 --> 01:41:40,683
Methinks I see thee, now thou art so low,>>

1362
01:41:41,023 --> 01:41:43,493
as one dead in the bottom of a tomb.

1363
01:41:44,563 --> 01:41:47,893
Either my eyesight fails, or thou look'st pale.

1364
01:41:50,203 --> 01:41:52,433
Then trust me, love,>>

1365
01:41:52,503 --> 01:41:55,034
in my eyes, so do you.

1366
01:41:55,084 --> 01:41:58,838
Dry sorrow drinks our blood.

1367
01:41:59,373 --> 01:42:01,433
Adieu.

1368
01:42:02,113 --> 01:42:04,173
Adieu.

1369
01:42:04,813 --> 01:42:07,573
Take thou this vial, being then in bed,>>

1370
01:42:07,653 --> 01:42:10,173
and this distilling liquor drink thou off.

1371
01:42:10,823 --> 01:42:13,883
No warmth, no breath, shall testify thou livest.

1372
01:42:14,893 --> 01:42:17,683
And in this borrowed likeness of shrunk death...>>

1373
01:42:17,923 --> 01:42:20,393
thou shalt continue two and forty hours,>>

1374
01:42:21,233 --> 01:42:24,163
and then awake as from a pleasant sleep.

1375
01:42:24,933 --> 01:42:27,333
What ho! Apothecary!

1376
01:42:30,543 --> 01:42:33,533
Come hither, man. I see that thou art poor.

1377
01:42:34,243 --> 01:42:36,963
Hold, there is 40 ducats.

1378
01:42:37,243 --> 01:42:40,443
- Let me have a dram of poison-- - Such mortal drugs I have,>>

1379
01:42:41,113 --> 01:42:44,843
but Mantua's law is death to any he that utters them.

1380
01:42:45,223 --> 01:42:48,743
- Art thou so-- - My poverty, but not my will, consents.

1381
01:42:54,593 --> 01:42:57,533
I pay thy poverty and not thy will.

1382
01:43:01,433 --> 01:43:03,633
Eyes, look your last.

1383
01:43:03,703 --> 01:43:06,473
Arms, take your last embrace.

1384
01:43:06,543 --> 01:43:08,873
And, lips,>>

1385
01:43:08,973 --> 01:43:11,913
oh, you, the doors of breath,>>

1386
01:43:12,513 --> 01:43:14,913
seal with a righteous kiss...>>

1387
01:43:16,883 --> 01:43:19,153
the dateless bargain...>>

1388
01:43:19,223 --> 01:43:21,743
to engrossing death.

1389
01:43:22,793 --> 01:43:25,623
Come, bitter conduct.

1390
01:43:25,693 --> 01:43:28,163
Come, unsavory guide.

1391
01:43:29,093 --> 01:43:31,563
Thou, desperate pilot, now at once...>>

1392
01:43:32,923 --> 01:43:35,633
run on the dashing rocks thy seasick weary bark.

1393
01:43:37,773 --> 01:43:40,293
Here's to my love!

1394
01:43:48,322 --> 01:43:52,623
Oh... true apothecary!

1395
01:43:55,323 --> 01:43:57,523
Thy drugs are quick.

1396
01:44:02,545 --> 01:44:05,393
Thus with a kiss...>>

1397
01:44:07,603 --> 01:44:09,733
I die.

1398
01:44:27,423 --> 01:44:29,823
Where is my lord?

1399
01:44:31,263 --> 01:44:35,323
I do remember well where I should be, and there I am. Where is my Romeo?

1400
01:44:35,493 --> 01:44:37,553
Dead!

1401
01:44:50,183 --> 01:44:52,233
What's this?

1402
01:44:52,313 --> 01:44:55,253
A cup, closed in my true love's hand?

1403
01:44:56,307 --> 01:44:58,633
Poison, I see,>>

1404
01:44:58,683 --> 01:45:01,353
hath been his timeless end.

1405
01:45:07,033 --> 01:45:09,363
Oh, happy dagger,>>

1406
01:45:09,663 --> 01:45:11,993
this is thy sheath.

1407
01:45:14,825 --> 01:45:18,293
There rest...>>

1408
01:45:18,373 --> 01:45:20,703
and let me die.

1409
01:45:27,513 --> 01:45:30,173
A glooming peace this morning with it brings;>>

1410
01:45:31,183 --> 01:45:33,983
the sun for sorrow will not show his head.

1411
01:45:35,723 --> 01:45:38,713
Go hence, to have more talk of these sad things.

1412
01:45:40,793 --> 01:45:43,063
Some shall be pardoned,>>

1413
01:45:43,133 --> 01:45:45,603
and some punished;>>

1414
01:45:46,233 --> 01:45:48,703
for never was a story of more woe...>>

1415
01:45:50,443 --> 01:45:53,173
than this of Juliet...>>

1416
01:45:54,173 --> 01:45:56,373
and her Romeo.

1417
01:46:23,728 --> 01:46:26,605
Bravo!

1418
01:46:30,317 --> 01:46:32,319
- Yea! Yea! - Yea!

1419
01:47:18,699 --> 01:47:21,410
- Bravo! - Yea! Bravo!

1420
01:47:35,973 --> 01:47:39,243
- God save the queen! - I arrest you in the name of Queen Elizabeth!

1421
01:47:40,483 --> 01:47:43,213
Arrest who, Mr. Tilney?

1422
01:47:44,553 --> 01:47:46,313
Everyone!

1423
01:47:46,383 --> 01:47:49,183
Admiral's Men, the Chamberlain's Men...>>

1424
01:47:49,823 --> 01:47:52,623
and every one of you ne'er-do-wells that stand in contempt...>>

1425
01:47:54,233 --> 01:47:57,023
of the authority vested in me by Her Majesty!

1426
01:47:57,703 --> 01:48:01,153
Contempt? You closed the Rose. I have not opened it.

1427
01:48:01,773 --> 01:48:04,278
That woman is a woman!

1428
01:48:04,328 --> 01:48:06,414
What?

1429
01:48:06,503 --> 01:48:09,233
A woman? You mean that goat?

1430
01:48:09,813 --> 01:48:13,273
I'll see you all in Clink, in the name of Her Majesty, Queen Elizabeth!

1431
01:48:15,313 --> 01:48:17,653
Mr. Tilney!

1432
01:48:23,863 --> 01:48:26,653
Have a care with my name. You will wear it out.

1433
01:48:35,533 --> 01:48:37,873
The queen of England does not attend...>>

1434
01:48:37,943 --> 01:48:40,403
exhibitions of public lewdness.

1435
01:48:40,473 --> 01:48:43,273
So something is out of joint.

1436
01:48:45,383 --> 01:48:48,573
Come here, Master Kent. Let me look at you.

1437
01:49:03,803 --> 01:49:06,263
Yes, the illusion is remarkable.

1438
01:49:06,803 --> 01:49:10,133
And your error, Mr. Tilney, is easily forgiven.

1439
01:49:10,843 --> 01:49:14,363
But I know something of a woman in a man's profession.

1440
01:49:14,943 --> 01:49:17,603
Yes, by God, I do know about that.

1441
01:49:19,643 --> 01:49:22,313
That is enough from you, Master Kent.

1442
01:49:27,423 --> 01:49:29,683
If only Lord Wessex were here.

1443
01:49:29,753 --> 01:49:31,883
He is, ma'am.

1444
01:49:34,752 --> 01:49:38,993
Y-Your Majesty.

1445
01:49:39,163 --> 01:49:41,833
There was a wager I remember...>>

1446
01:49:42,273 --> 01:49:45,533
as to whether a play could show the very truth and nature of love.

1447
01:49:47,173 --> 01:49:49,703
I think you lost it today.

1448
01:49:54,453 --> 01:49:57,713
You are an eager boy. Did you like the play?

1449
01:49:58,453 --> 01:50:01,783
I liked it when she stabbed herself, Your Majesty.

1450
01:50:08,033 --> 01:50:10,433
Master Shakespeare.

1451
01:50:13,033 --> 01:50:16,093
Next time you come to Greenwich, come as yourself,>>

1452
01:50:16,168 --> 01:50:19,643
and we will speak some more.

1453
01:50:36,723 --> 01:50:38,923
Your Majesty.

1454
01:50:40,443 --> 01:50:42,436
Why, Lord Wessex.

1455
01:50:42,486 --> 01:50:45,030
Lost your wife so soon?

1456
01:50:45,063 --> 01:50:47,723
Indeed I am a bride short,>>

1457
01:50:47,973 --> 01:50:51,103
and my ship sails for the new world on the evening tide.

1458
01:50:52,329 --> 01:50:54,915
How is this to end?

1459
01:50:54,943 --> 01:50:57,603
As stories must when love's denied-->>

1460
01:50:57,783 --> 01:51:00,454
with tears and a journey.

1461
01:51:00,504 --> 01:51:02,973
Those whom God has joined in marriage...>>

1462
01:51:03,053 --> 01:51:05,713
not even I can put asunder.

1463
01:51:06,594 --> 01:51:10,053
Master Kent.

1464
01:51:15,033 --> 01:51:18,623
Lord Wessex, as I foretold, has lost his wife in the playhouse.

1465
01:51:21,003 --> 01:51:23,523
Go make your farewell and send her out.

1466
01:51:24,873 --> 01:51:27,533
It's time to settle accounts.

1467
01:51:30,513 --> 01:51:33,443
- How much was that wager? - Fifty shillings.

1468
01:51:34,853 --> 01:51:36,963
Pounds.

1469
01:51:37,483 --> 01:51:40,683
Give it to Master Kent. He will see it rightfully home.

1470
01:51:49,533 --> 01:51:52,723
Tell Master Shakespeare something more cheerful next time...>>

1471
01:51:53,563 --> 01:51:55,953
for Twelfth Night.

1472
01:52:13,853 --> 01:52:16,323
Too late.

1473
01:52:25,703 --> 01:52:28,033
My Lady Wessex.

1474
01:52:42,913 --> 01:52:45,313
A hired player no longer.

1475
01:52:46,110 --> 01:52:48,738
Fifty pounds, Will,>>

1476
01:52:48,753 --> 01:52:51,153
for the poet of true love.

1477
01:52:52,393 --> 01:52:54,863
I'm done with theater.

1478
01:52:56,093 --> 01:52:58,623
The playhouse is for dreamers.

1479
01:52:58,733 --> 01:53:01,253
Look what the dream brought us.

1480
01:53:02,303 --> 01:53:04,963
It was we ourselves did that.

1481
01:53:06,303 --> 01:53:09,503
And for my life to come, I would not have it otherwise.

1482
01:53:10,643 --> 01:53:13,443
I have hurt you, and I'm sorry for it.

1483
01:53:14,883 --> 01:53:17,813
If my hurt is to be that you write no more,>>

1484
01:53:19,023 --> 01:53:21,483
then I shall be the sorrier.

1485
01:53:26,993 --> 01:53:29,723
The queen commands a comedy, Will,>>

1486
01:53:29,779 --> 01:53:31,653
for Twelfth Night.

1487
01:53:31,703 --> 01:53:33,893
A comedy.

1488
01:53:34,873 --> 01:53:36,893
What would my hero be?

1489
01:53:36,973 --> 01:53:39,703
The saddest wretch in all the kingdom, sick with love?

1490
01:53:42,643 --> 01:53:44,843
It's a beginning.

1491
01:53:46,213 --> 01:53:49,153
Let him be a duke, and your heroine-->>

1492
01:53:50,383 --> 01:53:53,183
Sold in marriage and halfway to America.

1493
01:53:55,553 --> 01:53:57,683
At sea, then.

1494
01:53:58,393 --> 01:53:59,793
A voyage to a new world.

1495
01:53:59,863 --> 01:54:02,523
A storm. All are lost.

1496
01:54:02,763 --> 01:54:04,963
She lands... on a...>>

1497
01:54:06,303 --> 01:54:08,703
vast and empty shore.

1498
01:54:10,773 --> 01:54:13,293
She's brought to the duke-->>

1499
01:54:14,213 --> 01:54:15,873
- Orsino.

1500
01:54:15,943 --> 01:54:18,073
- Orsino?

1501
01:54:18,383 --> 01:54:20,313
Good name.

1502
01:54:20,383 --> 01:54:23,573
But fearful of her virtue, she comes to him dressed as a boy.

1503
01:54:25,000 --> 01:54:29,283
And thus is unable to declare her love.

1504
01:54:30,893 --> 01:54:33,293
But all ends well.

1505
01:54:33,823 --> 01:54:35,628
How does it?

1506
01:54:35,678 --> 01:54:38,523
I don't know.

1507
01:54:39,203 --> 01:54:41,393
It's a mystery.

1508
01:54:48,213 --> 01:54:50,903
You will never age for me,>>

1509
01:54:50,983 --> 01:54:52,913
nor fade,>>

1510
01:54:52,983 --> 01:54:55,173
nor die.

1511
01:54:55,489 --> 01:54:58,623
Nor you for me.

1512
01:54:59,326 --> 01:55:02,383
Good-bye, my love.

1513
01:55:03,123 --> 01:55:05,453
A thousand times good-bye.

1514
01:55:10,254 --> 01:55:13,223
Write me well.

1515
01:55:44,663 --> 01:55:47,193
My story starts at sea,>>

1516
01:55:48,373 --> 01:55:51,303
a perilous voyage to an unknown land.

1517
01:55:53,003 --> 01:55:55,063
A shipwreck.

1518
01:55:57,983 --> 01:56:00,173
The wild waters roar and heave.

1519
01:56:02,913 --> 01:56:05,583
The brave vessel is dashed all to pieces,>>

1520
01:56:08,923 --> 01:56:11,393
and all the helpless souls within her...>>

1521
01:56:12,863 --> 01:56:15,053
drowned.

1522
01:56:17,833 --> 01:56:20,233
All save one:>>

1523
01:56:21,203 --> 01:56:23,393
a lady...>>

1524
01:56:24,773 --> 01:56:27,433
whose soul is greater than the ocean,>>

1525
01:56:29,113 --> 01:56:32,043
and her spirit, stronger than the sea's embrace.

1526
01:56:35,683 --> 01:56:38,013
